{"key":"processedPost-6139700","value":{"id":6139700,"first":6137032,"last":6140243,"when":1160143872,"utime":"10/06/06 05:11 PM","content":"You can't replace a 5\" thick aluminum and ceramic filter with a 1\" thick paper vacuum cleaner filter, regardless if it says 'hepa' or not.  There is much more involved.  You want a laminar flow hepa filter, which means it must be rated to withstand pressure on one side.  If you pressurized a paper filter, it would blow out.<br />RR","title":"Re: How to built a HEPA filter?"}}